Paper: hep-th/0003221

Date: 2000-03-24

Title: T-duality and Actions for Non-BPS D-branes

Authors: E.A. Bergshoeff, M. de Roo, T.C. de Wit, E. Eyras and S. Panda

Comments: Latex, 11 pages

Journal-ref: JHEP 0005 (2000) 009

We employ T-duality to restrict the tachyon dependence of effective actionsfor non-BPS D-branes. For the Born-Infeld part the criteria of T-duality andsupersymmetry are satisfied by a simple extension of the D-brane Born-Infeldaction.